GuoYu's Homepage Home Publications CV (pdf) Blog Guo, Yu (郭煜) Ph.D Student Department of Computer Science Donald Bren School of Information & Computer Science University of California, Irvine guo.yu(at)uci(dot)edu tflsguoyu(at)gmail(dot)com B.A → M.A → M.Phil → R.A → Ph.D ( Intern → Intern ) I am a 3rd-year Ph.D student in iGravi Lab, Department of Computer Science at University of California, Irvine, supervised by ZHAO Shuang. My interests include Computer Graphics and Vision, especially in material appearance modeling and physically based rendering. Before starting Ph.D, I was a member of BeingThere Centre and worked on several research projects at Nanyang Technological University (Singapore) as a Research Associate. I obtained my M.S in CS from Shenzhen Institute of Advanced Technology, Chinese Academy Sciences (Shenzhen, China), advised by HENG Pheng-Ann. And B.S in Mathematics from Central South University (Changsha, China).